Elecnor Agrees on a $677 Million Loan for Pair of Solar-Thermal Facilities

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-04-18T08:16:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/elecnor-agrees-475-million-euro-loan-for-two-solar-thermal-plant.html
Elecnor SA (ENO)  said in a regulatory
filing it agreed a 475 million-euro loan to build two 50-
megawatt solar-thermal power plants in Alcazar de San Juan,
southern Spain.  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  led a syndicate of nine
banks which also included Banco Santander SA,  Banco Popular
Espanol SA (POP)  and  Credit Agricole SA. (ACA)   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Sills at 
 bsills@bloomberg.net  